Your broader point

You’re highlighting something important:

Interpretation does not grant ontological status.

Humans often project meaning onto phenomena.

Examples:
	•	constellations in the sky
	•	myths attached to planets
	•	symbolic interpretations of natural patterns

These interpretations can be meaningful culturally without implying the universe itself shares those meanings.

