The muse analogy

Your idea that we might serve as a muse for some distant system is a poetic way of expressing relational meaning.

Meaning arises in relationships between observers and phenomena, not necessarily within the phenomena themselves.

In other words:
	•	stars influence human imagination
	•	humans might influence something else somewhere

But the meaning exists within the interpreting system.

